                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17022.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Barnum</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of War</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort Sam Houston</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following received from General Pershing: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Squad of Mexicans appeared this afternoon half mile east of international
                            bridge, deliberately fired towards American side, killing railroad car
                            inspector. <pb facs="0937" n="821" xml:id="pg_821"/> There had been
                            little firing and none toward American side. Am now covering whole river
                            front, and troops have orders to vigorously return any deliberate firing
                            from Mexican side.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Barnum.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
